  "text": "The PDZ domain of PICK1 has been shown before to interact with a variety of proteins [CITATION_1] 32 , and point mutations within the PDZ domain of lysine 83 (K83) or of both lysine 27 (K27) and aspartate 28 (D28) with alanines abolished protein binding [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] 34 . Since GST-RAB39B GTPgS pulled down fulllength myc-PICK with the K83A substitution (myc-K83A), but not with the K27D28AA substitutions (myc-KDAA), we concluded that K27 and D28 in the PDZ domain is key for the interaction of PICK1 with RAB39B (Fig. 2b) .",
